node.text:
Photos by Jassen Todorov @jassensf / The drought in the western United States is real and serious. I recently surveyed all major reservoirs in Northern California from above. In my 20 years of flying, I have not seen the state so dry. These two pictures depict Lake Berryessa and New Melones Lake, California's seventh and fourth largest reservoirs, respectively. Both images were taken while flying my single-engine Piper Warrior plane.
Nikon D810, 70-200mm. #YourShotPhotographer #california #drought #fromabove #aerialphotography

node.text:
Photo by Jenny Wong @jdubcaptures / In the high Canadian Arctic at approximately 73° N, an otherworldly landscape is revealed as the snow and ice retreat briefly for the summer. 
This place is called Qajuutinnguaq in Inuktitut. It is a short boat ride from the hamlet of Arctic Bay (Ikpiarjuk in Inuktitut), Nunavut, where we based ourselves for a few weeks. As we hiked around the raw landscape, our Inuit guide shared his knowledge passed down through oral stories over many generations. This place was once plentiful with char. But as the story goes, a military training camp dropped a grenade in one of the freshwater pools in the Adams River, and it was never quite the same. #YourShotPhotographer #Nunavut #Canada #InuitLand

node.text: Photo by @gretchenkaystuart / Nothing lifts the spirit quite like a misty mountain rainbow! World events feel really heavy these days. Spending time in nature has been scientifically proven to relieve stress and also reminds us that vast, wild places do still exist. It is important to protect them. This photo was captured in Glacier National Park with a 50mm lens. #glaciernationalpark #leavenotrace #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by @sarmistha_bera / I photographed this beautiful tailed jay butterfly at Central Park during my morning walk. Also called the green-spotted triangle, it belongs to the swallowtail family. It is hard to capture these butterflies because they are very active. 
90mm, macro lens. #YourShotPhotographer #macro #macrophotography #nature

node.text: Photo by @veronika_k_ko / I took this macro shot with a mobile phone at my neighborhood flower shop. I like to observe and enjoy flowers, communicating with them and capturing their beauty during their short lives. Especially in the summer, they are among my favorite subjects for photography. They are included in my photo series, Summer Vibes. I hope this beautiful flower can charge you positively! #YourShotPhotographer #flower #summer #fineartphotography #nature

node.text: Photo by @gabmejia / Witnessing this couple with matching jackets enjoy their time watching the sunrise at about 4,000 meters (13,000 feet) high on the tallest mountain in Taiwan was one of the loveliest sights I've seen. Indeed, love transcends even the tallest mountains. #YourShotPhotographer
